Q1) take user input of the length and width of rectangle and check if it is a square or not
Q2) take two values from the user and print the value which is bigger
Q3) Ask the user for quantity of items required, one item costs 100, if the user buy more than 1000 give them a 10%
discount
Q4)
A school has following rules for grading system:
a. Below 25 - F
b. 25 to 45 - E
c. 45 to 50 - D
d. 50 to 60 - C
e. 60 to 80 - B
f. Above 80 - A
Ask user to enter marks and print the corresponding grade.
Q5)
Write a program to print absolute value of a number entered by user. E.g.-
INPUT: 1        OUTPUT: 1
INPUT: -1        OUTPUT: 1
Q6)
A student will not be allowed to sit in exam if his/her attendence is less than 75%.
Take following input from user
Number of classes held
Number of classes attended.
And print
percentage of class attended
Is student is allowed to sit in exam or not.
Q7)
Ask user to enter age, sex ( M or F ), marital status ( Y or N ) and then using following rules print their place of
service.
if employee is female, then she will work only in urban areas.

if employee is a male and age is in between 20 to 40 then he may work in anywhere

if employee is male and age is in between 40 t0 60 then he will work in urban areas only.

And any other input of age should print "ERROR".
Q8)
A 4 digit number is entered through keyboard. Write a program to print a new number with digits reversed as of orignal
one. E.g.-
INPUT : 1234        OUTPUT : 4321
INPUT : 5982        OUTPUT : 2895